3 lrg roma tomatos
bunch fresh cilantro
5-6 oz. smoked mussles or shrimp (do not substitute)
2 minced peppers abodo sauce
2 tbs abodo sauce
ground cumin
white pepper
Mojo to taste w/ some of the roasted garlic minced
2 tbs fresh lemon juice
1 tbs of smokey hot sauce

Halve the roma tomatoes and place them lightly salted under salamander cut-side up until blackened. Press out the remaining water out of each and put the tomatos in the fridge to let cool. Put a rough chop on the tomatos when they are cool and combine the rest adding the cilantro at the end keeping their leaves whole. 
